## 1. Desktop Header Architecture & Dropdown Mapping
On desktop, your horizontal navbar will have **6 top-level menu items**. Hovering over the main categories will open structured dropdown columns to expose the deeper sub-pages detailed in the PDF.
### 🏠 1. Home
 * *Direct link to the Homepage.*
 * Contains your primary hero focus: **"Community Transformation Begins with Healing"**.
### ℹ️ 2. About Us [Dropdown]
 * **Our Story** *(Identity & Narrative)*
 * **What We Believe** *(The 6 Core Principles: Communities Lead, Healing Creates Transformation, etc.)*
 * **How We Work** *(The 5 Implementation Pillars)*
 * **Our Partners** *(PACJA, WFP, Landesa)*
 * **2025 Year in Review** *(Archival Media Hub)*
### 🧘‍♂️ 3. Programs [Dropdown]
*This track houses your long-term, ongoing community pillars.*
 * **Circle Keeper Training** *(The flagship microsite link)*
 * **Gender Equality & Social Inclusion** *(Includes SRHR, Menstrual Dignity, and School Greening initiatives)*
 * **Peace & Security** *(Covers the 130+ Healing Circles sessions and online safety)*
 * **Education, Youth & Digital Inclusion** *(Wolfram STEM programs & computational tracks)*
### 🚀 4. Projects [Dropdown]
*This track houses targeted, localized, or time-bound initiatives.*
 * **Climate Resilience** *(Overarching ASAL adaptation strategies)*
